Don't worry if you're not flexible or can't do the poses perfectly. The motto of Fightmaster Yoga is "It's not about the pose". You don't have to be perfect.

All you have to do is show up. When you make the decision to take care of yourself, all sorts of amazing things begin to happen. You have more energy. You become more patient. Your outlook on life becomes more positive. And all of these changes you will experience in this yoga journey will begin to affect those around you in ways you never dreamed possible. 

This practice can bring a loving, positive energy that will spread throughout your world. And as you deepen your yoga practice you will have the opportunity to meet many like minded souls like yourself who are also laying down their mat and doing the work.

-Laozi

3a_6SJZLg5M.title: Be Thankful #shorts
3a_6SJZLg5M.description:
Be thankful that you don’t already have everything you desire.
If you did, what would there be to look forward to?

Be thankful when you don’t know something,
for it gives you the opportunity to learn.

Be thankful for the difficult times.
During those times you grow.

Be thankful for your limitations,
because they give you opportunities for improvement.

Be thankful for each new challenge,
because it will build your strength and character.

Be thankful for your mistakes.
They will teach you valuable lessons.

Be thankful when you’re tired and weary,
because it means you’ve made a difference.

It’s easy to be thankful for the good things.
A life of rich fulfillment comes to those who
are also thankful for the setbacks.

Gratitude can turn a negative into a positive.
Find a way to be thankful for your troubles,
and they can become your blessings.

~Author Unknown

M3HMFpdDxjI.title: Hatha Yoga For Gratitude - Remembering Lesley Fightmaster
M3HMFpdDxjI.description:
Beloved followers and friends,
This is Duke, Lesley's husband. I am saddened to share that my beautiful wife and your beloved yoga teacher passed away unexpectedly on November 21, 2020. At this time, my children and I are surviving a tremendous amount of grief and pain. While our family is focusing inward, I know her memory lives on via this platform. Please know that Lesley loved all of you and was deeply devoted to sharing her passion with each of her students. In Lesley's honor I am releasing the last video she recorded for this community. She had created it with the intention of bringing a bit of gratitude and love to all of you on Thanksgiving. I hope it will bring you some comfort in this difficult time. I ask that you hold our family in your hearts and in your blessings. Our family would appreciate that you honor our need for privacy. 
With love,
Duke

20 minute full body yoga stretch to help you become your authentic self. For another great full body yoga stretch try this one https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EZfRR19MMpo&list=PLEs9dX8UXFZq97dEPT0UzWSw8M6npoWiE&index=2&t=18s

For the complete Hatha Yoga Joy 30 day challenge click this playlist here https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLEs9dX8UXFZrato6TEhWDIDbo8V3hL67w 

This is day 10 of Hatha Yoga Joy. The full HYJ 30 day program is also on http://www.myyogapal.com with extra daily assignments to increase your inner joy along with a community of supporting yogis. 

To try MyYogaPal for 7 days for just $1 click here https://www.myyogapal.com/offers/H5VRN4Sj

#fullbodyyoga #fullbodyyogastretch #fightmasteryoga

Get extra strength to perform yoga poses you never thought possible by strengthening your core by clicking here  https://www.myyogapal.com/core-sign-up and check out our most popular videos here https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLEs9dX8UXFZr49caXzoog429B-C742_Wk

If you want to feel better in your body this is the channel for you. Because when you practice yoga you feel better!

Don't worry if you're not flexible or can't do the poses perfectly. The motto of Fightmaster Yoga is "It's not about the pose". You don't have to be perfect.

All you have to do is show up. When you make the decision to take care of yourself, all sorts of amazing things begin to happen. You have more energy. You become more patient. Your outlook on life becomes more positive. And all of these changes you will experience in this yoga journey will begin to affect those around you in ways you never dreamed possible. 

This practice can bring a loving, positive energy that will spread throughout your world. And as you deepen your yoga practice you will have the opportunity to meet many like minded souls like yourself who are also laying down their mat and doing the work. 

Consider subscribing to this channel and become a part of making this world shine with more light!

If you practice even 10 minutes a day I guarantee you will feel better. 

Subscribe to this channel because yogi's around the world have changed their lives for the better and you can too.

Welcome to the Fightmaster Yoga channel! 

Yoga videos to make you feel better.

Life is hard. 

I know what it feels like to be overwhelmed, overweight and either depressed or stressed out. I've been there.

My name is Lesley Fightmaster. I am a yoga teacher trainer. I have taught thousands of classes. I've seen amazing transformations in people just like you.

New to yoga? Try my 30 day yoga for beginners and beginners yoga playlists.

For a yoga workout try my hatha yoga happiness program or yogafix90. Also find yoga for weight loss, total body yoga, vinyasa yoga, and Ashtanga classes. Each class is a full body yoga stretch.

You might also enjoy my detox yoga, energizing yoga, morning yoga or yin yoga for deep stretching.

If you practice even 10 minutes a day I guarantee you will feel better. 

Subscribe to this channel because yogi's around the world have changed their lives for the better and you can too.  #yoga #Hatha #vinyasa

For more details please visit Our Website - www.fightmasteryoga.com

QHMyXBBMDaA.title: Why I don't do "Hot Yoga"
QHMyXBBMDaA.description:
I know...EVERYONE loves hot yoga! I just can’t do it. Watch this video for normal temperature yoga https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bAFQLda6AEE&t=3s

I wanted to like it. I know there are a lot of great benefits from the heat. But after giving it a shot these were my main complaints:

I kept almost blacking out. The room would start spinning. Everything began to go dark. I had to sit down. My friend, Amber, actually had a seizure in a Bikram class several years ago. The ambulance and EMT's took her out on a stretcher. The teacher just kept the class going.

It’s hard to know how flexible you are. The heat makes your body extra limber. This might seem good until you over stretch. The possibility for injury is greater when you're body is that hot.

The teachers can be kind of mean. I noticed multiple hot yoga teachers pointing out student's mistakes to the class. It seemed that modifications we not welcome. It kind of scared me.

 
I know some people love hot yoga (but it’s not for me). I may have just had some bad experiences. It was a long time ago (probably 1997-ish), so things could be different now. The very first yoga classes I ever went to were at a Bikram studio. My friends were really into it and I had been wanting to try yoga. I was sooooo disappointed because I didn't realize there were other styles of yoga. I was super happy to find that wasn't the case. And...BTW, I actually know a couple of hot yoga teachers who are very sweet. 

If you want to practice normal temperature yoga I recommend www.myyogapal.com  

Love,

Lesley

Welcome to the Fightmaster Yoga channel! 

Yoga videos to make you feel better.

Life is hard. 

I know what it feels like to be overwhelmed, overweight and either depressed or stressed out. I've been there.

My name is Lesley Fightmaster. I am a yoga teacher trainer. I have taught thousands of classes. I've seen amazing transformations in people just like you.

New to yoga? Try my 30 day yoga for beginners and beginners yoga playlists.

For a yoga workout try my hatha yoga happiness program or yogafix90. Also find yoga for weight loss, total body yoga, vinyasa yoga, and Ashtanga classes. Each class is a full body yoga stretch.

You might also enjoy my detox yoga, energizing yoga, morning yoga or yin yoga for deep stretching.

If you practice even 10 minutes a day I guarantee you will feel better. 

Subscribe to this channel because yogi's around the world have changed their lives for the better and you can too.  #yoga #Hatha #vinyasa

Welcome to the Fightmaster Yoga channel! 

Yoga videos to make you feel better.

Life is hard. 

I know what it feels like to be overwhelmed, overweight and either depressed or stressed out. I've been there.

My name is Lesley Fightmaster. I am a yoga teacher trainer. I have taught thousands of classes. I've seen amazing transformations in people just like you.

New to yoga? Try my 30 day yoga for beginners and beginners yoga playlists.

For a yoga workout try my hatha yoga happiness program or yogafix90. Also find yoga for weight loss, total body yoga, vinyasa yoga, and Ashtanga classes. Each class is a full body yoga stretch.

You might also enjoy my detox yoga, energizing yoga, morning yoga or yin yoga for deep stretching.

If you practice even 10 minutes a day I guarantee you will feel better. 

Subscribe to this channel because yogi's around the world have changed their lives for the better and you can too.  #yoga #Hatha #vinyasa

6BP1Eo5g-TM.title: 20 Minute Yoga Flow Vinyasa Class (intermediate) | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
6BP1Eo5g-TM.description:
20 Minute Yoga Flow Vinyasa Class (intermediate). Today's vinyasa flow yoga class is intermediate and leads to the peak pose called eka pada koundinyasana (aka scissors pose). I have also created a playlist of yoga practices for each day of the week here https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLEs9dX8UXFZqjEiNK8M1c6A6SQ0xZCSp1 Eka means "one," "pada" means foot and Koundinya was a scholar who became a buddhist monk after learning about the "middle way" from the Buddha. To practice the yoga pose eka pada koundinyasana we need to warm up the hips and shoulders with vinyasa flow. We also need to connect to our core muscles to find the "middle way." Scissors yoga pose is less about strength and more about leverage and balance. I find the idea of a fulcrum to be helpful. Remember being at the playground enjoying the teeter-totter or seesaw with a friend? It was important that you both weighed about the same amount and it was also important that one of you didn't decide to hop off while the other was in the air! Remember when you could find that perfect balance?  It was pretty effortless, right? There's a center point in the peak yoga pose eka pada koundinyasana that you'll find after practicing vinyasa for a while. You find it in your body. Balance. The Middle Way. You may need to test the extremes first to find balance, but once you've tested the extremes. you'll find that the point of balance will come with much less effort. Lean yourself forward enough to get your back leg to lift. If you don't have the flexibility to straighten your front leg, don't worry...you can practice the posture with the front leg bent. Most importantly, practice with your breath, attention and intention and enjoy the journey. Yoga poses come and poses go...enjoy the ride. If you enjoyed this 20 minute vinyasa flow yoga class at the intermediate level visit fightmasteryoga.com for a free yoga class everyday. xoxo

rtWKG2ldJOM.title: 1 Hour Vinyasa Flow (Live Yoga Class) 💕To Handstands | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
rtWKG2ldJOM.description:
1 Hour Vinyasa Flow Live Yoga Class 💕To Handstands. This live yoga class hour-long free video is brought to you by our Patreon Comunity. My yoga videos are to keep you strong and healthy. My mission is to surround you with a supportive Fightmaster Yoga community.

Handstands are difficult and can be scary to attempt whether it's in a live yoga class or not. You've seen beautiful photos or yoga videos of others doing handstands. You might be thinking, "why can't I do it?" "What's wrong with me?!?"

But, the truth is that doing a handstand isn't the "goal" of this free yoga video because yoga is never about the pose.

I know handstands are difficult. I've been practicing them for years and still struggle sometimes.

I'll teach you my tips and tricks in this full length live yoga video about practicing them safely. Remember, if you have any injuries in your back, shoulders or wrists, handstands aren't for you right now. If you're on your monthly cycle, or; if you have glaucoma, uncontrolled blood pressure, or had a recent surgery, skip the handstand part. Put your legs up against a wall instead...you'll get great benefits as you take care of yourself.

Here are some steps to practicing handstands:
1. Put on some comfy clothes, grab your yoga mat, blocks and strap.
2. Clear away a space to practice yoga that includes access to a wall.
3. Do your best and let go of any expectations.

Remember, handstands are challenging. It doesn't matter if you get into one or not. If just matters that you keep your breath steady while giving it your best effort. When you focus on your breath and best effort, you mind will become quieter and you'll feel strong and connected.

Help me make more hour-long yoga videos by becoming a Patreon member! Visit www.patreon.com/fightmasteryoga for more info. Our Patron community is a great way to deepen your yoga practice by asking me questions during our LIVE monthly video calls.

If you enjoy this yoga video, become a subscriber. Click the subscribe button and the notification bell. Join our supportive Fightmaster yoga community and hit the "like" button too! Leave a comment on this youtube video and them comment on three other people's comments. Support other Fightmaster Yogi's!

When you're a Fightmaster Yogi who practices yoga regularly, you'll be healthy and strong. When you're healthy and strong, you can support and help others along the way.

When you don't practice yoga, you don't feel as well.

With regular practice you'll be healthy and strong. People will want to be around you and you'll be so glad to be there for them!

77Rhu1Pa0IM.title: 20 Minute Morning Yoga Flow (AM For Energy) | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
77Rhu1Pa0IM.description:
20 Minute Morning Yoga Flow (AM For Energy) is a great way to start the AM of the day. So energizing yoga for morning is here for you! We'll begin this YouTube yoga class seated, to settle into our morning yoga practice and we'll start with a breathing practice (kabalabhati breath). Remember, when practicing kabalabhati breath, the inhales are passive and the exhales are more pronounced and forceful through the nose. Do remember to inhale though! If you don't, you'll run out of breath. I heard someone describe this type of breathing practice as blowing a candle out through the nose. We'll practice 3 rounds of this breath and it's great for warming the body up and for increasing energy throughout the body. Next we'll begin moving, slowly warming up and getting the body ready to (yoga) flow. We add yoga standing poses like warrior 2, reverse warrior and side angle. These standing yoga postures help to strengthen and stretch the legs and hips. If you happen to sit a lot (at a desk, in a car, etc...like most of us),  practicing these standing yoga poses help to keep the body flexible and strong. Next we'll come into a dynamic variation of twisted triangle / wide legged forward fold twist. Twisting is great anytime but in the morning there's added benefit to get the digestion "moving.' After the standing posture, we begin some yoga backbends or extension of the spine. These postures will really increase and move your energy throughout your body, so enjoy. After our backbends, we'll unwind with some forward folds and gentle twists to re-balance the spine. Then our final resting poses...savasana to help you relax this morning. Try to stick with your whole savasana because it's sooooo important to integrate your whole morning yoga practice. Most importantly, have a great morning and day! :-)

b7BnOGStDDY.title: 1 Hour Yoga Flow Vinyasa (Live class) | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
b7BnOGStDDY.description:
1 Hour Yoga Flow Vinyasa free live yoga class with Fightmaster yoga. This live, free, heart opening yoga flow was filmed during a Fightmaster Yoga retreat in magical Sedona, AZ at Angel Valley. One of our yoga retreat group requested to practice Urdvha Dhanurasa (upward facing bow pose, also known as "wheel"). To prepare for this challenging vinyasa yoga posture, we must correctly warm up and educate our bodies. In this vinyasa flow, we do that by stretching the shoulders, upper back, and hip flexors. It's also important to keep the belly muscles engaged, the hip bones lifting toward the lower ribs and the sitting bones lengthening toward the backs of the knees as you spiral your inner thighs in toward each other. These actions will keep stability in your lower back, preventing too much arch there. Remember to practice deep backbends mindfully. Take your time and rest whenever you need to. This free hour long youtube yoga practice is brought to you by our Fightmaster Yoga Patreon community. If you like my hour long free yoga videos, become a Patreon supporter and help me make them!

zdwwnwI3DLU.description:
20 Minute Yoga For Strength And Core Workout (upper body). This free yoga video is 20 minutes and was made to help you create a healthy habit. A yoga fix. Fightmaster yoga is the best place on youtube to find any yoga class that meets your needs. If you want to get strong and build more strength through yoga then this is your youtube go to yoga channel. If you want to find yoga for abs and core workouts then Fightmaster Yoga is the perfect fix. If you want to build flexibility you are in the right place. We deliver free youtube yoga videos every Monday. Remember to subscribe to the Fightmaster Yoga channel and hit the bell so you never miss a free full yoga vinyasa class. We have yoga videos of every length to fit into your schedule. Fightmaster yoga is the best place to develop a home yoga practice. We are also developing a new subscription app called yoga fix 30. Comment below what you would like to see on our Fightmaster yoga app. Thanks. Enjoy! Yoga for strength and flexibility with core focusing on the upper body. This free yoga video is 20 minutes and was made to help you create a healthy habit. A yoga fix. We'll begin with an affirmation to get you into the right mind-set for your practice. Affirmations are wonderful tools to help create positivity throughout your life and when used regularily, you'll absolutely notice a difference in how you feel. If you like this affirmation, or if you find any affirmations that really resonate with you. Take a moment to write them down and practice saying them and writing them 10 to 15 times per day. After the opening of our class, we'll warm up our shoulders and triceps. Next, we'll start to strengthen. You might find the triceps strengthening in reverse table (purvottanasana variation) to be challenging. I found it challenging as well! Always do the best you can and rest whenever you need to. Push the pause button! We'll move to table position next and practice some balance, as we practice stabilizing the core muscles and then we'll start to strengthen the core muscles as well. There are a lot of chatturanga push-ups in this class. If you find it to be too much, please practice them with your knees on the mat or hold plank position. If you continue practicing this video, you'll get to the point where you can do all of them.

IKhigMLVQt0.title: 1 Hour Total Body Yoga Workout (Vinyasa Flow to Bird Of Paradise) | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
IKhigMLVQt0.description:
1 Hour Total Body Yoga Workout (Vinyasa Flow to Bird Of Paradise). Today’s free one hour total body yoga video will prepare you for this challenge posture Bird of Paradise. In order to be ready to attempt Bird of Paradise, we need to warm up and educate many parts of the body, including our shoulders, hips, hamstrings and core muscles (total body yoga). There’s a slight twist in the yoga posture as well and we’ll be practicing some twisting postures that will help to keep the pelvis and hips neutral and we twist the spine from above the waist. Balance is also a component of practicing Bird of Paradise. We’ll start off balancing in tree pose and you’re always welcome to practice tree instead of moving into Bird of Paradise if it seems too difficult in today's yoga practice. Remember, balance is different day to day. One day your balance will feel solid and stable, another day it will feel frustratingly impossible. Don’t take it personally...most days it falls in between the two extremes. Yoga asanas or postures are a great way to keep your total body strong and flexible. localized.title: 1 Hour Total Body Yoga Workout (Vinyasa Flow to Bird Of Paradise) | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
localized.description:
1 Hour Total Body Yoga Workout (Vinyasa Flow to Bird Of Paradise). Today’s free one hour total body yoga video will prepare you for this challenge posture Bird of Paradise. In order to be ready to attempt Bird of Paradise, we need to warm up and educate many parts of the body, including our shoulders, hips, hamstrings and core muscles (total body yoga). There’s a slight twist in the yoga posture as well and we’ll be practicing some twisting postures that will help to keep the pelvis and hips neutral and we twist the spine from above the waist. Balance is also a component of practicing Bird of Paradise. We’ll start off balancing in tree pose and you’re always welcome to practice tree instead of moving into Bird of Paradise if it seems too difficult in today's yoga practice. Remember, balance is different day to day. One day your balance will feel solid and stable, another day it will feel frustratingly impossible. Don’t take it personally...most days it falls in between the two extremes. Yoga asanas or postures are a great way to keep your total body strong and flexible. When connected with your breath, your yoga practice helps to unblock energy in your body and increase the circulation so that your total body and mind stay healthy and active. tNew4h1LTcs.description:
20 Minute Full Body Yoga Stretch (Quickie) For Total Body Flexibility. This free yoga class is a yoga stretch quickie designed to stretch your muscles and make you more flexible. Many people don't have time to make it to a live yoga class. Some people don't even have time to practice YouTube yoga videos every day. Maybe it's because they think a yoga class has to be an hour long to get the benefits of stretching. The truth is it is better to practice yoga for 5 minutes a day than 1 hr once a week. The goal is to stretch every day. This is how you achieve flexibility and strength. If you search Fightmaster yoga 20 minute classes or Fightmaster Yoga quickies then you will find many YouTube yoga videos that you can easily fit into your schedule. Practice yoga and stretch everyday. These YouTube videos will help you strengthen and increase flexibility in your total body. h7_zFeXmqUg.title: 20 Minute Hatha Yoga (Heart Opening Flow Yoga) ...You DID IT!! Day 30  | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
h7_zFeXmqUg.description:
20 Minute Hatha Yoga (Heart Opening Flow Yoga). Today is a heart opening yoga flow. Welcome to day 30!! You did it!! If you weren't already addicted to yoga, I bet that you are now!! Congratulations on continuing to practice until the end! If it took you 30 days, that's great! If it took you 300 days to get here, that's awesome too! You did it and I'm so proud of you!  This vinyasa flow will focus on opening the upper back and stretching out the whole front of your body. When practicing any backbending posture, be sure to keep a slight internal rotation in your legs (as if you're holding a bock between your thighs), lengthen your butt bones toward the backs of your knees, draw your front bottom ribs down toward your waist, lift your back ribs up toward your head and widen your collarbones. Enjoy your flow and be sure to thank yourself for a job well done! Join me this summer in Greece: http://www.fightmasteryoga.com/new-events/2018/6/30/2018-greece-retreat
And/Or Join me this summer in Morocco: http://www.fightmasteryoga.com/new-events/2018/7/8/2018-morocco-retreat

If you want to continue tomorrow with me, I'll be on Patreon....I've created 7 additional classes for our Patreon supporters. The classes are designed to connect with the Chakras, so each class focuses on each of the 7 chakras. Chakras are energy centers that are located along the spine. Sometimes they get blocked and then energy can't flow freely which prevents us from feeling our best. Join me at www.patreon.com/fightmasteryoga to enjoy these classes as well. If you can choose to pledge any amount (minimum $1 per month) and you're a member with full access to everything on our site. Enjoy!!! xoxoxo, Lesley

0SCFHSbrBow.title: 20 Minute Yoga Flow Vinyasa (Hip Openers, Twists and Arm Balances) Day 29 | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
0SCFHSbrBow.description:
20 Minute Yoga Flow Vinyasa (Hip Openers, Twists and Arm Balances) Day 29 includes some "challenge" poses or as one of my teachers called them, "party tricks!" This flow is challenging, so if you're not able to practice the more difficult poses, don't worry...these poses take time and patience. I've fallen out of them many times and I was struggling with one of the arm balances (Astavakrasana) during this video. I don't spend much time on any of them to keep the video to 20 minutes, but I encourage you to push the pause button and practice them longer. Most importantly, have fun!!

15 Minute Guided Meditation for Anxiety and Over-Thinking Day 28. Today's video is a guided meditation for relaxation and detachment from over-thinking. You've worked hard all week and now it's time to relax a bit. We'll start with some gentle movement followed by a guided meditation where we'll visualize some time spent walking and relaxing at the beach. This meditation is also great to reduce anxiety and to help the mind to become quieter. Join me in Greece, Amsterdam and/or Morocco this summer!! m7JhGM8EmV4.title: 20 Minute HIIT Yoga Class (Cardio with Balance Fun!) Day 25 | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
m7JhGM8EmV4.description:
20 Minute HIIT Yoga Class (Cardio with Balance Fun!) Day 25. Today's video is a HIIT class, but there's some fun balancing in it as well...I've been receiving a lot of positive feedback that you're enjoying the challenging of balance poses although some days are more successful in balancing than others. I'm happy to report that my experience with balancing is the same and today you'll get to witness some of my wobbling. I hope it does't throw off your balance too much!! Remember...have fun with it and if you fall out, just keep going. I have a friend who sometimes says when she teaches..."did you see that trophy in th back of the class today? That's right...there's isn't any trophy for 'best yoga performance', so just breathe and enjoy your practice!"

4TPwcRV98B0.title: 20 Minute Yoga Flow Vinyasa (Legs and Back) Day 24 | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
4TPwcRV98B0.description:
20 Minute Yoga Flow Vinyasa (Legs and Back) Day 24. Our vinyasa flow video today is sequenced to focus on strengthening and stretching your legs and back. We'll move though a warm up including bidilasana (cat/cow) and then we'll practice sun salutations and standing poses. As we move through our standing poses today, be sure to keep your focus on your legs so that they're aligned and engaged. We'll make our way to to the floor as we practice some back strengthening back bends like salabhasana (locust pose) and dhanurasana (bow pose). Remember to keep your hip points lifting toward your lower ribs, your sitting bones lengthening toward the backs of your knees and lifting your inner thighs toward the ceiling. Also, lift your lower belly in and up. Enjoy!!!
Yoga Teacher Training is an amazing, life-changing experience regardless of whether you want to become a teacher or you just love yoga and want to deepen your practice. I'm finally hosting my own signature Yoga Teacher Training in beautiful Southern California overlooking the beach. For more information, visit www.fightmasteryoga.com/ytt and enter your email address. I'd love to see you!

Ak7aKPbmuqg.title: 20 Minute Yoga Flow Vinyasa to Forearm Balance (Pincha Mayurasana) Day 20  | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
Ak7aKPbmuqg.description:
20 Minute Yoga Flow Vinyasa to Forearm Balance (Pincha Mayurasana). Get your YogaFix! Today we'll stretch and strengthen the upper back and shoulders to get you ready for Pincha Mayurasana or forearm balance. Be sure to use a wall to balance if you're going upside down (I didn't have a wall so I used a tree...a wall works much better lol)! Remember, if you have back injuries, shoulder or neck injuries, uncontrolled high blood pressure, glaucoma or if it's during your moon cycle, it's not advised to practice inversions.

_1ZuHzO8_sA.title: 20 Minute Hatha Yoga (Workout For Core Strength) Day 5 | Fightmaster Yoga Videos Fix 30
_1ZuHzO8_sA.description:
20 Minute Hatha Yoga (Workout For Core Strength) Day 5. A hatha yoga class where our focus is again on those core muscles. You can expect some more Agni Sara pranayama practice...notice if it's a bit easier today...no judgement, just notice! Every day you're getting stronger. Some days you might feel it and other days you might not, but you are. We're also going to practice bakasana or crow pose. This is a fun arm balance that many people love, even though most of us find it super challenging. Remember, it doesn't matter if you're able to do the pose. The only thing that matters is giving it your best shot today. If you balance or not doesn't matter because when you try your best, your mind is focused and quiet and that's where we experience "yoga." See you tomorrow!!! BTW--I finally have my own signature teacher training program If you're interested in becoming a yoga teacher, want to deepen your yoga practice or you just love yoga, I encourage you to join me because it's absolutely life-changing: fightmasteryoga.com/ytt

If you're interested in purchasing your own Love Big Journal by my teacher Diana Christinson. You can find it here: https://www.amazon.com/Love-Big-Journal-Diana-Christinson/dp/0692939571

A0DnaQsWx5o.title: Yoga Fix 30 - 30 Days of 20 Minute Yoga Videos  | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
A0DnaQsWx5o.description:
Yoga Fix 30 - 30 day yoga challenge with 20 minute yoga videos of vinyasa flow classes for beginners and intermediate yogis. Get addicted to yoga...Fightmaster style! This year, I've created a new 30 days of yoga classes for Strength and flexibility. YogaFix30 is the best way to deepen your yoga practice and have fun. Similar to your YogaFix90 program from a few years ago. When I created YogaFix90, I had no idea of the impact that it would have on our community! Many of you have told me that you've taken that journey multiple times and have created groups around it, connecting and practicing together. YogaFix30 will get you inspired to continue practicing daily, or if you're new to the channel, you can begin your yoga addiction here! Be sure to opt in for the free daily emails which will include our daily quotes and additional "homework" suggestions to enhance your journey: http://www.fightmasteryoga.com/yogafix30

All of our quotes are from Diana Christinson's beautiful "Love Big" journal. For even more journaling activities to connect deeper to yourself and others, purchase your copy here: https://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_ss_i_3_9?url=search-alias%3Daps&field-keywords=love+big+journal&sprefix=Love+Big+%2Caps%2C216&crid=4HQLDSZJ6QTP

All of the affirmations are from Louise Hay's classic book, "You can Heal Your Life." 

Fightmaster Yoga is made possible by the support of generous yogi's like you. Join the community https://patreon.com/fightmasteryoga At the conclusion of our 30 day program here, you'll have access to 7 additional yoga videos that will ONLY be available to Patreon supporters!

Oxo229b9vjw.title: 1 hour Hatha Yoga (full class) | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
Oxo229b9vjw.description:
1 hour Hatha Yoga (full class) is thanks you to our Fightmaster Yoga Patreon community! For every 50 new patreon members, I'll make a full one-hour class. This is our 5th one!!! Hatha Yoga is a term used to describe any type of yoga that includes asanas or postures. This class includes sun salutations, standing poses such as triangle (trikonasana), half moon (ardha chandrasana), twisted triangle (parivrtta trikonasana), and twisted half moon (parivrtta ardha chandrasana). This class also includes some pranayama toward the end (nadi shodhana) and a short meditation for a complete yoga experience! Enjoy, and don't forget to join me on Patreon. xoxoxo, Lesley

B2oD5mGd0Hs.title: 50 Minute Total Body Yoga Workout (For Your Birthday) | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
B2oD5mGd0Hs.description:
50 Minute Total Body Yoga Workout (For Your Birthday). Happy birthday to you! If it's not your birthday today, then happy un-birthday...either way, let's practice some yoga together. We happened to film this video on my birthday, so thank you for sharing my birthday with me! We'll focus on inversions because as we celebrate our journeys around the sun, our bodies become more and more affected by gravity. Inversions help us to counter those effects (like spinal compression, etc). Any yoga pose or posture where the head is lower than the heart is considered an inversion, so get ready for lots of forward folds, downward dogs and maybe even a handstand or two!

VZ3i6s56PQA.title: 20 Minute Morning Yoga (Vinyasa Flow) | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
VZ3i6s56PQA.description:
20 Minute Morning Yoga (Vinyasa Flow) is such a nice way to start the day. Many of you asked me to make a new morning flow, so here you go! We made this video in beautiful Sedona and I just love it there! We traveled and camped in a JUCY van...it really does include just about everything you need...even the kitchen sink! If you're going on a trip, check them out: - www.jucyusa.com

Morning Yoga is Fresh and the perfect way to start the a amezing day! This full morning yoga practice offers an opportunity for you to ease in, slowly building on breath for a well rounded practice. Show up to pranayama (or breath practice) and a moving meditation that lovingly wakes up mind and body, providing you the energy you need to conquer your day. Legs, Hips, heart, shoulders to feet. Cultivate healthy flow of energy through the spine. Use your breath to build strength, to move with intention and to Find What you Feels Good. 

Don't forget to like and subscribe because we need to know that you're enjoying the videos!

NC7dZcdmL5I.title: Vinyasa Flow Morning Yoga for Energy
NC7dZcdmL5I.description:
Vinyasa Flow Morning Yoga for Energy is a 40 minute class for waking up or the afternoon and even the evening if you're not trying to go right to sleep afterwards. You'll move through a sequence to strengthen and stretch your whole body as well as some pranayama (breathing exercises) to get the oxygen moving through your whole body.

This morning yoga practice will help you tune in to your mindful side and set intentions with awareness and breath. ZZAZS4d7KZI.title: 20 Minute Full Body Yoga Stretch for Flexibility (no more low back pain!) | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
ZZAZS4d7KZI.description:
20 Minute Full Body Yoga Stretch for Flexibility (no more low back pain!) | Fightmaster Yoga Videos Is an all-levels Vinyasa Flow class. Enjoy this class in the morning or anytime of day. If you do a lot of sitting for work or if you drive a lot, put this class in your regular rotation. Sitting causes the hip flexor muscles to shorten and many people experience the lower back over-arching (moving the pelvis into an anterior tilt) which causes lower back pain. Practice this yoga video regularly to relieve pain from sitting. Thanks to Jess Lancaster for requesting this class. Thank you for telling your friends about me!!! Spreading the word to people you know is the very best compliment.

Holding hands, hugging, getting a massage, etc releases oxytocin (sometimes called, "the cuddle hormone") which calms emotions and can actually reduce the brain's ability to feel pain! So, hug it out!

jPJjOfj-d1g.title: 40 Minutes Hatha Yoga Happiness: Never take anyone personally Day 10 | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
jPJjOfj-d1g.description:
40 Minutes Hatha Yoga Happiness: Never take anyone personally Day 10. Today's topic/tool is to never take anyone personally. Many times we react to other people's issues when there's absolutely no need. We all have pain inside of us. Sometimes, someone will come along and trigger it with words, or a look or actions. If we didn't have that pain already within us, the situation wouldn't even bother us and the same it true for others. They have the pain of an old wound within them and we say or do something to trigger it. They lash out at us, but unless we're deliberately trying to be hurtful, the situation really isn't about us at all and there's no reason to take it personally or to be hurt. Open the hips, the shoulders and tap into your core strength. This vinyasa yoga practice tones the legs and the arms while offering a strong foundation to protect the joints. Be mindful and meet your edge! Return to this practice to experience your growth and deepen your practice.

More total body workouts here https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLEs9dX8UXFZq528QJjY2zzk6NGqkzVpuE Subscribe to our channel http://bit.ly/1mzfCpl Check out Align - "A must have alignment course for all yogis practicing at home.": https://fightmasteryoga.vhx.tv/ Save $20 using the coupon code "LOVEYOURSELF"
Support Fightmaster Yoga by liking and sharing on your social media!

This class will get your heart rate up and will burn some calories. We'll stretch our shoulders, hip flexors and hamstrings. We'll also focus on strengthening our core muscles so we can gain a new perspective by going up side down. Please be careful with yourself (as always). This is YOUR practice and there's never any reason to push. If you have uncontrolled high blood pressure, glaucoma, or if you're on your moon cycle, please avoid handstands and other inversions. You may opt to lie down and put your legs up against a wall instead.

Do you mostly practice yoga at home? If so, we want to be sure that your alignment is the best it can be. This 8 hour course will teach you how to align your body safely in the poses that we frequently practice: http://www.fightmasteryoga.com/8hr-alignment-course/

Visit fightmasteryoga.com and join our mailing list to keep in touch! Also, I've added a new link to "stuff I like." Many people ask me about what kind of mat, blocks, straps, etc that I like to use. I'm compiling some of my favorites here: http://www.fightmasteryoga.com/stuff-i-like/ 

Please donate: https://www.paypal.com/donate/?hosted_button_id=VNCTTYTH5MX2C

For Amazon purchases please use this link http://www.amazon.com/?tag=fightyoga-20

Please subscribe! http://bit.ly/1mzfCpl

All your strength comes from the core. Get my free core class here https://www.myyogapal.com/core-sign-up and develop strength where you need it most.

Welcome to the Fightmaster Yoga channel! 

Yoga videos to make you feel better.

Life is hard. 

I know what it feels like to be overwhelmed, overweight and either depressed or stressed out. I've been there.

My name is Lesley Fightmaster. I am a yoga teacher trainer. I have taught thousands of classes. I've seen amazing transformations in people just like you.

New to yoga? Try my 30 day yoga for beginners and beginners yoga playlists.

For a yoga workout try my hatha yoga happiness program or yogafix90. Also find yoga for weight loss, total body yoga, vinyasa yoga, and Ashtanga classes. Each class is a full body yoga stretch.

You might also enjoy my detox yoga, energizing yoga, morning yoga or yin yoga for deep stretching.

If you practice even 10 minutes a day I guarantee you will feel better. 

Subscribe to this channel because yogi's around the world have changed their lives for the better and you can too.  #yoga #Hatha #vinyasa


Filmed at http://www.pacificashtanga.com

http://fightmasteryoga.com/

zwVPntQi3KE.title: My 8hr Alignment Course is Now Available - Yoga | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
zwVPntQi3KE.description:
https://www.myyogapal.com

In this course, you'll get exclusive access to TEN 30 minute classes. Each class is designed to enhance the lecture on the poses that we're studying but the classes are also well-rounded. We'll begin with  the heart of the practice, the breath and then we'll practice the "blueprint" pose for all of our standing poses, Tadasana or Mountain Pose.  Next, we'll breakdown and practice warror 2, triangle pose, half moon pose and tree pose. You'll learn all of the sanskrit names for the poses as well. We will practice and learn the components to Surya A and B (Sun Salutations). There is a full section on inversions including handstands, headstands and forearm balance as well as shoulderstand.  We'll also look at and practice some arm balances.  The course is like a mini-teacher training! I'll be sharing with you tons information that I've learned and taught as a teacher trainer!!

Here's what students are saying about the course:
"Just wanted to say how much I'm enjoying your course Lesley it's invaluable for someone like me who practices using your YouTube videos at home without an instructor. It's giving me a lot more confidence in making sure I am aligned properly. So much gratitude."
-Kathleen O.

Ellie:  I'm really enjoying the course. I'm learning a lot and hopefully adjusting some old bad habits that I have acquired along the way. Finding that I don't have to square my hips has made some poses far more accessible and much less of a struggle. A shorter stance in trikonasana has made it easier to place the weight more in my big toe, something I always struggled to understand or do before. The videos are paced really well for me, I can digest the information at the same time as practicing. I'm eager to keep learning more about alignment which may explain why I'm going through the videos quickly. 

Mohammed R.: “Lesley is an amazing teacher I have learnt yoga thru her youtube channel and to get deeper I have joined this course so far I have enjoyed every moment of being a good student. I would highly recommend it to anyone"

The course is designed for everyone, but if you're a beginner, please don't attempt the more difficult postures until you feel that you're ready. Be sure to post in the message boards so that we can keep our community thriving!!! I hope to see you on the message boards soon!! Join me on your mat! xoxo, Lesley

30 Minute Yoga Full Body Stretch Workout For Energy (Chakra) Vinyasa Flow  is a full body workout focusing on the first three chakras.  Here's a playlist with more total body workouts https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLEs9dX8UXFZq528QJjY2zzk6NGqkzVpuE Subscribe to Fightmaster Yoga http://bit.ly/1mzfCpl

The first (root) chakra is associated with our security:for example, feeling secure and connected to our families and financial security. The second (Sacral) chakra is associated with our relationships, creativity and emotional security.  The third (solar plexus) chakra is concerned with our self-esteem and our personal power. Many times these lower chakras are blocked or weak. This class addresses those energy centers to begin the healing process.

PUaAb8s7sdU.title: Vinyasa Flow Yoga for Weight Loss
PUaAb8s7sdU.description:
Vinyasa Flow Yoga for Weight Loss (40 minute Workout) is a heat building class that will help you to burn lots of calories.  Yoga for weight loss playlist https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLEs9dX8UXFZqlraDmrxxuPfKPPSjccdan Subscribe to Fightmaster Yoga http://bit.ly/1mzfCpl

I struggled with making a yoga for weight loss class for a couple of reasons: first, pretty much all yoga helps with weight loss but the even more important factor is what we eat.  I can practice all the yoga in the world but if I eat tons of refined sugar and processed foods, I won't lose any weight and I'll probably gain it.  Second, our mind is very important when it comes to weight loss. The more we can love and accept ourselves the way that we are, the easier weight loss will be.  So, come for the vanity and stay for the sanity! :-) Thank you for all of your donations!! If you can afford to help us with our mission of bringing yoga to as many people as possible, please use the link below to send us a donation through PayPal:

Please donate: https://www.paypal.com/donate/?hosted_button_id=VNCTTYTH5MX2C
Please subscribe! http://bit.ly/1mzfCpl

Please visit fightmasteryoga.com and join our mailing list! We're headed to Ojai, CA in August for a yoga and Reiki healing retreat.  My wonderful healer, Tina from Pink Rose Healing will be joining us all the way from Australia.  Please email me for info or to sign up: lesleyfightmaster@gmail.com

All your strength comes from the core. Get my free core class here https://www.myyogapal.com/core-sign-up and develop strength where you need it most.

Welcome to the Fightmaster Yoga channel! 

Yoga videos to make you feel better.

Life is hard. 

I know what it feels like to be overwhelmed, overweight and either depressed or stressed out. I've been there.

My name is Lesley Fightmaster. I am a yoga teacher trainer. I have taught thousands of classes. I've seen amazing transformations in people just like you.

New to yoga? Try my 30 day yoga for beginners and beginners yoga playlists.

For a yoga workout try my hatha yoga happiness program or yogafix90. Also find yoga for weight loss, total body yoga, vinyasa yoga, and Ashtanga classes. Each class is a full body yoga stretch.

You might also enjoy my detox yoga, energizing yoga, morning yoga or yin yoga for deep stretching.

If you practice even 10 minutes a day I guarantee you will feel better. 

Subscribe to this channel because yogi's around the world have changed their lives for the better and you can too.  #yoga #Hatha #vinyasa


Filmed at http://www.pacificashtanga.com

qJzfZ6w0s4g.description:
Ashtanga Yoga Primary Series with Jessica Kass and Lesley FIghtmaster. Here's a playlist with more Ashtanga classes https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLEs9dX8UXFZp_HD_IXcEGlC9PapjOA40y Subscribe to Fightmaster Yoga http://bit.ly/1mzfCpl

This class has been requested by a lot of people and we hope that you like it.  It's not intended for beginners.  This class was made for intermediate and advanced yoga practitioners who want to practice a led Ashtanga Class in their own home.  The method is based on the teachings of Sri K. Pattabhi Jois where the Vinyasas are counted in Sanskrit and the names of the poses are also in Sanskrit.  The breath count is included as well but there isn't much instruction on how to practice the poses as this practice is meant to be a moving meditation without many distractions. If you're newer to Ashtanga, please start with either the 30-minute: https://youtu.be/vBaQlOq1KoU or the 60-minute practice: https://youtu.be/2wYN1IhnXT4

9vsElhE6tAo.title: 30 Minute Yoga For Flexibility | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
9vsElhE6tAo.description:
30 Minute Yoga For Flexibility is a class designed to keep the natural curves in our spine.  For More flexibility and stretching classes click here https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLEs9dX8UXFZrDO3Vjr5XCl3amfpn1lqwS Subscribe to Fightmaster Yoga http://bit.ly/1mzfCpl

It's better not to over-exaggerate the curve in the lower back or to pop our rib cage out.  It's best to create length as we balance these areas.  The body will go into the "path of least resistance." So, if the shoulders are tight, when we raise the arms up by the ears, the low back will over-arch and the front ribs will puff out.  If this happens consistently, there is a chance of injury to the lower back.  This class is designed to counter that tendency so that we can keep our lower back safe.

mRgeFEuXfmQ.title: Yoga for Stress Relief and Depression
mRgeFEuXfmQ.description:
40 Minute Yoga for Stress Relief and Depression Workout was requested by smets072. For more vinyasa flow classes click here https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLEs9dX8UXFZqUrWHYNvFU5wU9_Ixci3Vg Subscribe to Fightmaster Yoga http://bit.ly/1mzfCpl 

I thought of ways to put this class together. One thing that really helps me when I feel depressed or stressed is to practice affirmations.  My favorite ones are by Louise Hay.  I've been using her affirmations for many years.  I incorporated a few different ones during this practice and also focused on a lot of chest expanding/heart opening poses to help boost our mood. This class is suitable to most levels.

If you want to feel better in your body this is the channel for you. Because when you practice yoga you feel better!

Don't worry if you're not flexible or can't do the poses perfectly. The motto of Fightmaster Yoga is "It's not about the pose". You don't have to be perfect.

Welcome to the Fightmaster Yoga channel! 

Yoga videos to make you feel better.

Life is hard. 

I know what it feels like to be overwhelmed, overweight and either depressed or stressed out. I've been there.

My name is Lesley Fightmaster. I am a yoga teacher trainer. I have taught thousands of classes. I've seen amazing transformations in people just like you.

New to yoga? Try my 30 day yoga for beginners and beginners yoga playlists.

For a yoga workout try my hatha yoga happiness program or yogafix90. Also find yoga for weight loss, total body yoga, vinyasa yoga, and Ashtanga classes. Each class is a full body yoga stretch.

You might also enjoy my detox yoga, energizing yoga, morning yoga or yin yoga for deep stretching.

If you practice even 10 minutes a day I guarantee you will feel better. 

Subscribe to this channel because yogi's around the world have changed their lives for the better and you can too.  #yoga #Hatha #vinyasa

Welcome to the Fightmaster Yoga channel! 

Yoga videos to make you feel better.

YVLddIO9Or8.title: Vinyasa Flow Yoga for Stress Relief: Yin and Yang
YVLddIO9Or8.description:
Vinyasa Flow Yoga for Stress Relief: Yin and Yang is a 40 minute class for everyone.  Just in time for the holiday season to help us let go of stress.  This can be a difficult time of year for many.  This class starts with a "Yang" practice which heats up the body.  Yang is associated with heat and light.  It is male-dominated energy according to Chinese philosophy.  Much of our world seems to be Yang dominant.  Where I live in Southern California, there is so much Yang energy.  A lot of competition to succeed...to "keep up with the Joneses" and to work, work, work.  This creates stress for many.  Our bodies spend way too much time in the "fight or flight" mode which wreaks havoc on our physical and emotional systems.  Yin is the feminine passive energy associated with cold and darkness.  It is a calming energy that allows us to relax and renew ourselves.  Yin is as important as Yang and we need both in order to find balance in our lives and in our bodies and minds.

I highly recommend reading "The Alchemist" by Paulo Coelho.  It's a wonderful "hero's journey" that describes the importance of following your heart's desire, or dream, or "Personal Legend."  It's so important to follow your heart to find your "Dharma" or what you were meant to do with your life.  By following this, we all add love to the world. 
To check out "The Alchemist" on Amazon:  
goo.gl/iJ36er Thank you for your support!! :-)

HYQQfos8GsM.title: 30 Minute Hatha Yoga for feet, ankles and calves | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
HYQQfos8GsM.description:
30 Minute Hatha Yoga for feet, ankles and calves is a great class for anyone.  It's so important to bring awareness to our feet...most of the time, our foundation for many yoga poses plus we spend a great deal of time on our feet.  If you wear shoes a lot (like most of us) then the muscles of the feet begin to atrophy.  If you've mostly worn shoes for many, many years and you begin yoga later in life, you'll probably have a difficult time balancing until you start to strengthen the muscles in your feet.  Ankles and calves need to be strengthened as well to keep us supported.

Please comment if you would like to see a certain type of class.  Please like and share this class if you're enjoying free yoga.  

If you're interested in becoming a yoga teacher or if you love yoga and want to stay safe in your practice and delve deeper into the yoga sutras, please email me: lesleyfightmaster@gmail.com

LJuy93g1HO4.title: 20 Minute Yoga Flow Vinyasa class to "twist it on out!" | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
LJuy93g1HO4.description:
20 Minute Yoga Flow Vinyasa class to "twist it on out!" Is a 20 minute class focused on twists.  Twists are great to help keep our spine healthy and lubricated and to help aid in proper digestion.  Always remember to inhale and lengthen your spine first, before exhaling into the twist.  Twists should be performed above the waist while keeping the hips and pelvis neutral.  By keeping the pelvis stable and neutral, we'll avoid the tendency to "crank" the lower back into the twist.  The low back will twist a little but the majority of the twist should be in the mid to upper back.  As always, rest when you need to rest and if you experience any pain, please stop.

If you're interested in teacher training, please send me an email: lesleyfightmaster@gmail.com
I'm scheduled to teach a 200-hour weekend format (12 weekends) beginning January 2015 and a month-long intensive training beginning July 2015.

1bS2o8Dzj4Q.title: 30 Minute Yoga Flow Vinyasa Yoga Overhand Grip (Bow) with Shireen Kaviani | Fightmaster Yoga Videos
1bS2o8Dzj4Q.description:
30 minute Vinyasa Yoga Overhand Grip in Dhanurasana (Bow) pose with Shireen Kaviani.  This is an intermediate to advanced class leading to Padanguthasana Dhanuransana.  Shireen does a beautiful job with this difficult variation of Dhanurasana.  In order to get into this pose, the shoulders, upper back and hip flexors need to be warmed up.  Please pay attention to your body.  The full pose is advanced.  If it isn't available to you today, stay with regular bow pose.  Stop if you experience any pain.  Shireen has a beautiful practice and she's very flexible, so she makes it look easy.  I have tightness in my shoulders which makes this pose really difficult for me.  It's a pose that I don't practice very much because if I don't get my shoulders and hip flexors open enough, my lower back gets too compressed...ouch!! This is why we get to see our lovely Shireen practice this pose! 

As always, work at your own pace, rest if you need to rest and stop if you experience any pain. Please like and share this class if you enjoy it! Thank you for all of your support!! I love our "Fightmaster Yoga" community.  If you have an idea for a class, please leave it in the comments below.  Thank you for all of your lovely comments!!! 

If you're interested in Yoga Teacher Training (I had the pleasure of having Shireen a few years ago in Teacher Training) or if you would like to join us on our Ladies Yoga retreat off the coast of Cancun February 19-25, please email me: lesleyfightmaster@gmail.com

Please donate if you can afford to.  We're saving for a new computer because ours is old and is starting to die.  We want to continue to make and upload weekly free yoga videos, and we've had a few problems recently. Blessings to you! xoxoxo
